body:
The following should compile, but [doesn't](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=a20ae3d0ae616eb820dc3cf1128c8fb6&version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2015):

```rust
use std::{marker::PhantomData, mem};

pub struct Example<T>(PhantomData<T>);

impl<T> Example<T> {
    fn example(&self) {
        const _X: usize = mem::size_of::<T>();
    }
}
```

It fails with the following error:

```
error[E0401]: can't use type parameters from outer function
 --> src/lib.rs:7:42
  |
5 | impl<T> Example<T> {
  |      - type variable from outer function
6 |     fn example(&self) {
  |        ------- try adding a local type parameter in this method instead
7 |         const _X: usize = mem::size_of::<T>();
  |                                          ^ use of type variable from outer function

error: aborting due to previous error

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0401`.
error: Could not compile `playground`.

To learn more, run the command again with --verbose.
```

Note that changing the const to use a let [allows the function to compile](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=0c9f25d55fe48da2a033b8c1319025ad&version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2015)

```rust
use std::{marker::PhantomData, mem};

pub struct Example<T>(PhantomData<T>);

impl<T> Example<T> {
    fn example(&self) {
        let _x = mem::size_of::<T>();
    }
}
```
